responses.text:
O God! Thou art my God alone;  
When shadows fall and hope is flown,  
My heart, in silence, seeks Thy face,  
Yearning for Thy boundless grace.  

Through desert lands my spirit thirsts,  
For living waters, quenched and nursed;  
Thy steadfast love, a morning sun,  
That lights my path till day is done.  

Though storms may rise and tempests roar,  
I cling to Thee forevermore;  
No other refuge do I claim—  
My soul exalts Thy holy name.  

O God! Thou art my God alone;  
Within Thy presence, I am known;  
My joy, my strength, my guiding light—  
I rest in Thee through every night.
